===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}} {{liushu|p}} {{och-l|民|the people}}: the oracle bone script forms resemble an eye pierced by a cross-shaped sharp implement. The graph may be connected with eye impairment or unclear vision, compare {{och-l|泯}}, {{och-l|眠}}, and {{och-l|眄}}; the ''Shiji'' has {{zh-x|視眩眠而無見兮|the sight was dizzy and dim, and nothing could be seen}}, while the ''Hanshu'' writes {{l|zh|泯}} for {{l|zh|眠}}.

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*r-mi(j)-n||people, man, human being}}. Cognate with {{cog|bo|མི}} and {{cog|dz|མི}}.

